 experiences of two gendered cancers -- tNarratives of long-term loneliness: case study of two older men -- tSupporting social inclusion in community-dwelling men with dementia -- tFuture directions in studies of ageing, men and social relations -- tIndex0 arestricted accessuhttp://purl.org/coar/access_right/c_16ecfonline access with authorization2star  aWhile there has been a gradual increase in scholarship on men, ageing and masculinities, little attention has been paid to the social relations of men in later life and the implications for enhancing their social wellbeing and counteracting ageist discourse. Bringing together scholars in social gerontology and the social sciences from across Global North and South nations, this collection fills the gaps in key texts by foregrounding older men’s experiences. It provides new perspectives across the intersections of old age, ethnicities, class and sexual and gender identity, paying particular attention to older men from seldom heard or marginalised groups.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aAgingxSocial aspects. 0aOlder menxAttitudes. 0aOlder menxSocial life and customs. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Gerontology.2bisacsh1 aAcelino Francisco Luz Nunes Queiroz, Artur, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCalasanti, Toni, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aElliott O’Dare, Catherine, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFrancisco Lopes de Sousa, Álvaro, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFutterman, Andrew M., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGilbert, Leah, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGraetz Simmonds, Janette, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/